 Aerial photo taken on Nov. 30, 2021 shows the Yangbaoshan bridge during a static load test in Guiding County, southwest China's Guizhou Province.  (Photo by Deng Gang/Xinhua)  GUIDING, Dec. 1 (Xinhua) -- The Yangbaoshan bridge in Guiding County of southwest China's Guizhou Province carried out a static load test on Tuesday. Forty-eight large trucks with a total of 1,680 tonnes of goods were parked on the bridge to test the construction quality and mechanical properties of the bridge structure. With a main span of 650 meters, the grand bridge, which is a part of the Guiyang-Huangping Highway, stretches 1,112 meters in length.  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 30, 2021 shows the Yangbaoshan bridge during a static load test in Guiding County, southwest China's Guizhou Province.  (Photo by Deng Gang/Xinhua)  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 30, 2021 shows the Yangbaoshan bridge during a static load test in Guiding County, southwest China's Guizhou Province.  (Photo by Deng Gang/Xinhua)  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 30, 2021 shows the Yangbaoshan bridge during a static load test in Guiding County, southwest China's Guizhou Province.  (Photo by Deng Gang/Xinhua)  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 30, 2021 shows the Yangbaoshan bridge during a static load test in Guiding County, southwest China's Guizhou Province.  (Photo by Deng Gang/Xinhua)â– 